===Etymology===
{{Han etyl}}
{{Han compound|肰|火|t1=dog meat|t2=fire|ls=ic}}: to burn. 肰 is also phonetic. The derivative [[燃]] stands for the original word in Modern Chinese.

Note that the upper left component is analyzed as 肉 (meat), and in the character 肰 (used as phonetic) is drawn as 月 (moon), but in 然 this is distorted (tilted), looking more like 夕 (evening), with an extra stroke; compare [[祭]], [[將]].

